review_blob:
Pours amber with no head.
Nose shows caramel and cardboard notes as well as some spicy hops.
Flavours include bready malt, soft spicy hops and a non-deScript bitterness in the slightly metallic finish.

Pours gold with a large head.
Nose shows mandarin, pear and apple notes along with some soft bready malt.
Flavours include more apple and overripe pear along with some soft doughy malt.

Pours gold with a large quickly fading head.

Flavours include bready malt, light grainy notes, as well as spicy and fruity hops.

Pours black with a small head.
Nose shows heavy roast, mint, earl grey herbal notes. Interesting stuff.
Flavours include more herbal earl grey notes and some of the roasted malt.

Pours red-tinged with a quickly fading head.

Flavours include massive doughy wheat notes, soft acidity, faint floral and berry notes.

Pours amber with a large head.
Nose shows heavy piny and resinous hops along with a fair whack of clean sweet malt.
Flavours include more pine and resinous hops, a fair bit of booze and more sweet clean malt.

Pours red with a quickly fading head.

Pours gold with a small head.
Nose shows herbal coriander notes, doughy wheat and little else.

review_blob:

review_blob:

Flavours include more toasty malt, caramel and some light spicy and herbal hops.

Nose shows funky notes, blueberry, soft woody oak. Some tropical fruit notes too interestingly enough.

Nose shows grapes, funk, horseblanket, woody oak.

Pretty much flat.

Pours brown with a small head.

Flavours include nutty malt, coffee grounds and sweet bready notes.

review_blob:
Pours amber with a large head.
Nose shows funky, fruity and earthy Brett notes along with spicy and herbal hops.
Flavours include more Brett, some grassy hops and finishes exceedingly dry.
Carbonation is insanely high.

review_blob:

Flavours inlcude grainy malt, spicy hops and bready notes. Easy drinking.

Flavours include more spicy and earthy hops along with grainy and bready malt. A bit of a non-deScript sweetness rolls through later unfortunately. Overall pretty good though.
